hopobject.body: Do you know what extension he's on? medical test systems incorporated Health economist Daniel McFadden of the University of California at Berkeley and colleagues have parsed the Medicare Part D data more finely. "The sickest people, with the most to gain, signed up early in the initial enrollment period, but lots of people waited to enroll at the very end," he said. "The take-up rate was the lowest among people who were fairly healthy, poorly educated and had low incomes."
